&gt; A little cleaner approach would be to set them in lists and have the
&gt; tests iterate over the lists.  Each test method then iterates over the
&gt; list of Components and performs its asserts/fails on each 
&gt; member of the
&gt; list.  This list is most cleanly initialized in the abstract test&#39;s
&gt; setUp().  Of course that means that every time you execute a test, you
&gt; re-initialize the list of components (I would prefer that), but if you
&gt; don&#39;t want to do that use the TestSetup class.
&gt; 
&gt; There is really no need for embedding a class definition in the suite
